This paper deals with variational autoencoders (VAEs) applied to natural language processing (NLP) tasks, which suggests that the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the training difficulties of VAEs, which could fall under categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper proposes a new scheduling scheme for training VAEs, which could also be relevant to categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.CV (Computer Vision).
